      About this item

      • Office desk chair for home office, work station, or conference room
      • Adjustable seat height, adjustable seat angle, and tilt control for customizable comfort
      • Supports up to 275 pounds; sturdy KD metal base; certified by BIFMA, a nonprofit organization that creates voluntary standards to support safe standards for business and institutional working environments
      • Puresoft PU upholstery in Black; contoured padded seat, backrest, and armrests for comfort; durable caster wheels for smooth-rolling mobility
      • Assembly instructions included; components (casters, base, arms, seat mechanism, hardware kit) arrive packed in the back cushion
      • Product Dimensions: 23.75 x 26 x 38.25 - 42 inches (WxDxH); seat width: 19.5 inches; seat depth: 17.75 inches; arm height: 26.25 - 30 inches

          Michael Plaskett
          5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, good-looking-comfortable enough -- and it rolls.
          Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
          Color: BrownVerified Purchase
          This is a good chair. It could be more cushily padded but sitting in it for any length of time is OK. Fine.

          Assembly:

          You have to fuss with it a little bit to get the seat cushion, the back and the two arm rests to mate up. They are unwieldy. It's the arm rests that tie the seat and back together. Screws are used to fasten the arm rests. You want to position the arm rests and upholstery pieces so as to perfectly line up the holes through which each screw will go. The screw threads will engage after the screws pass all the way through the holes.

          You need to start the screws loosely in order to allow enough play to mate up the four main pieces. Once they are all hanging together they tighten together quite sturdily.

          Each screw needs quite a few turns before the screws eventually tighten down. The included wrench works fine. "Hand tight" it says on the sticker on the screw package. You want to make the screws pretty darned tight.

          This AMAZON chair rolls fine when you want to move it. Our first chair came from IKEA. We discovered on using it that its casters are made NOT TO ROLL if you are not seated in the chair. To move the chair for vacuuming or for crawling under the desk for something you dropped, you must drag or lift up the chair. All the IKEA chairs are like this, apparently.

          The base of the Amazon chair assembles easily. Insearting the casters into the base unit took some strength and a bit of finesse. The mechanicals work OK -- although we have not yet figured out how to adjust the seat's inclination. Maybe it does not incline.

          It comes in brown, white and black; we like the blackish brown.

          At first I thought I just put this together badly but after reading some other reviews it seems like a common issue, some holes don't line up right with each other. I tried my best to make it work but one screw on the arm of the chair just wont go in properly even though the other screws on the same are connected perfectly with the base of the chair. This also makes moving in the chair veryyyy squeaky. It is very comfortable though, and stable so I never feel like it will break despite its bad screws. Doesn't allow you to lean back, though, but you can adjust the height dramatically which makes up for it. Overall good chair, it took me about an hour to put together and I'm happy enough to not return it!

          Amazon Customer
          4.0 out of 5 stars Surprisingly Excellent
          Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2023
          Color: CreamVerified Purchase
          After several hundreds if not thousands of dollars spent buying chairs for my business and home office that were extremely uncomfortable and downright horrible I decided to give Amazon a chance and bought this chair a few days ago. I was shocked at the excellent quality and how easy it was to put together. The chair is very sturdy and all screws and metal base holes align perfectly. The instructions are intelligently clear and easy to follow. Unfortunately, the seat leans forward/down and so it pushes me off the chair. I read several reviews and although Ive seen others report having the same issue apparently, however its a small number of complaints.
